Workers of a macadamia factory in Embu on Monday boycotted work, protesting against failure by the management to pay them their three-month salary.The employees of Limbua Kithungururu Macadamia factory, Embu North subcounty, held a demo in the afternoon chanting anti-management songs.Most of the staff said their houses have been locked by their landlords for failing to pay rent. &ldquo;For the last three months, the factory&rsquo;s management has been lying to us that they would pay us our dues, but the pledges have been empty,&rdquo; said a staff who did not want to be named for fear of reprisal . Area MCA Ibrahim Swale met the workers and promised he would follow up the matter with their bosses. Embu county is the biggest producer of macadamia nuts in Kenya.